Warren Tufts https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warren_Tufts 0 Chester Warren Tufts (December 12, 1925 – July 6, 1982), best known as Warren Tufts, was an American comic strip and comic book artist-writer best known for his syndicated Western adventure strip Casey Ruggles, which ran from 1949 to 1954.
